Sunday 17 September — 7:30PM

Dara Ó Briain

Doc Brown

Glenn Wool

Jarred Christmas

Dara O Briain, one of the most charismatic, intelligent, fast-talking and downright funny live performers working today makes his Greenwich Comedy Festival debut. The king of audience interaction heads to the Big Top where he’ll relish exchanging ultra-rapid fire quips with members of the audience, and delivers witty and daring anecdotes like no other stand-up comedian.

A master-class in intelligent stand-up…It’s thoughtful stuff, impeccably delivered. With material this strong, you don’t need gimmicks The Guardian
Joining Dara is an unmissable supporting cast with Comedian/Rapper, Taskmaster star and bloody good entertainer Doc Brown, globe trotting story-weaver Glenn Wool and Kiwi comedy-hero Jarred Christmas as host.
